race.comment: DEVIL RIDER (2) has switched to the in-form Seib yard on a 27-day return. He disappointed at Newcastle last time but was only beaten 1.6L this trip at Hawkesbury prior. This is winnable if presented on song and the betting moves should tell the story. WAL'S ANGELS (1) will be fancied building on his comfortable win this grade at Moruya over a mile. Tackles a middle distance for the first time. Lugs more weight but Owen stays aboard and he should be right in it. DEVILS DAUGHTER (6) has been around the mark since her win here three back. Has to be considered. VIESTE (3) has been disappointing for a while but has a 3kg claim today and is on a quick backup. Capable of getting some on the minor spoils.
